Complementarity and limits of the different technics of pancreatic morphologic investigation for the diagnosis of acute pancreatitis and complications (author's transl). The authors have previously proposed the endoscopic retrograde cholangio-pancreatography as a technic to be used systematically in acute pancreatitis it offers a precise diagnosis of microlithiasis and a possibility of an immediate endoscopic treatment. They have studied the pancreatographic patterns in 355 cases of clinical acute pancreatitis